- ## Dealing
#Dealing #with #Vagueness #Challenges #Requirements #Engineering 
In this paper, we propose a verification method of the unambiguity, the consistency, the completeness, and the redundancy of NFRs in SRS written with a natural language. We can detect ambiguous, inconsistent, incomplete, and/or redundant NFRs with our method. We also developed a prototype system based on the method.

- ## Specifying
#Specifying #Quality #Model #Integrating #FRs  #NFRs #Software #Engineering 
We introduce a new requirements frame to represent time-response requirements. We provide one action, that is, “respond “ and its three cases, that is, “agent case,” “goal case,” and “condition case.” The agent case corresponds to a noun that responds. The goal case corresponds to performance objective in response. So, goal case should be quantitative attributes.
